    "narrative": "The Zurich Zebras are positioned for a high-ceiling performance today, headlined by **Yordan Alvarez**, who anchors the roster with an elite 87.42 efficiency score. The matchup against Lorenzen offers an ideal environment, bolstered by a +14% park factor and the premium production expected from the #2 hole. Alongside him, **Pete Crow-Armstrong** (71.81) and **Trea Turner** (69.86) serve as vital engines for our scarcity-driven strategy. **Pete Crow-Armstrong** benefits significantly from a favorable platoon setup against Boyle, while **Trea Turner** remains a must-start despite the minor efficiency tax imposed by catcher pop times; his leadoff role and elite speed profile are indispensable in our quest to dominate the SB category. **Colt Keith** (69.64) and **Caleb Durbin** (65.57) also provide significant value, with **Caleb Durbin** benefiting from a highly exploitable matchup against the soft-tossing Drohan (10.13 xERA).\n\nThe benching process was particularly tight at the margins, with **Jerar Encarnacion** (42.21) presenting the most compelling case for late inclusion. Ultimately, he was squeezed out by the sheer volume of high-efficiency starts across our utility and outfield slots, as his matchup against Nola lacks the upside of our active starters. We are closely monitoring the risks associated with **Christian Yelich** (54.08), whose score is suppressed by wind concerns and a tough draw against Sonny Gray; while he is currently in the lineup, his proximity to the 50-point threshold makes him a pivot candidate if late-breaking weather reports worsen. Similarly, while **Logan O'Hoppe** (43.41), **Kazuma Okamoto** (42.45), and **Josh Smith** (42.75) are active, their proximity to the \"Below floor\" designation requires careful observation; should their game environments deteriorate, we will prioritize preserving daily game caps over forcing mediocre production from the bottom of the order.",
